Package org.ipdr.protocol

Contains implementation of all IPDR protocol messages

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
ProtocolMsgIdentification Some base methods for all protocol messages: used to dispaly information about them.
 

Class Summary
ProtocolData Various methods for getting data from IPDR/CRANE records and putting data into IPDR/CRANE records.
ProtocolDataBigEndian Implementation of ProtocolData for big endian byte order
ProtocolFieldTypes The class concentrates XDR field types and lengths
ProtocolInfo Represents a protocol info record of the discovery message
ProtocolMsg The class represents a common parent for all protocol messages
ProtocolMsgCONNECT The class represents a CONNECT message.
ProtocolMsgCONNECT_RESPONSE  
ProtocolMsgDATA The class represents a DATA message.
ProtocolMsgDATA_ACK The class represents a DATA_ACK message.
ProtocolMsgDISCONNECT  
ProtocolMsgEmpty The Java encapsulation of an empty message (typically produced by a timeout event when reading).
ProtocolMsgERROR The class represents an ERROR message.
ProtocolMsgFINAL_TEMPLATE_DATA_ACK The class represents a FINAL_TEMPLATE_DATA_ACK message
ProtocolMsgFLOW_START  
ProtocolMsgFLOW_STOP  
ProtocolMsgGET_SESSIONS The class represents a GET_SESSIONS message.
ProtocolMsgGET_SESSIONS_RESPONSE The class represents a GET_SESSIONS_RESPONSE message.
ProtocolMsgGET_TEMPLATES The class represents a GET_TEMPLATES message.
ProtocolMsgGET_TEMPLATES_RESPONSE The class represents a GET_TEMPLATES_RESPONSE message The message has the following structure: struct GetTemplatesResponse { struct IPDRStreamingHeader header; short requestId; short configId; TemplateBlock currentTemplates <>; } A TemplateBlock has the following structure: struct TemplateBlock { short templateId; // ID of Template - context within configId // Provides numeric Identifier to // IPDR service specification for context of // Session/config UTF8String schemaName; // Reference to IPDR service specification UTF8String typeName; // Reference to IPDR service specification FieldDescriptor fields<>; // Fields in this Template } A FieldDescriptor has the following structure: struct FieldDescriptor { int typeId; // ID of Field Type int fieldId; // unqualified Field code that can be used // as alternative accessor handles to Fields UTF8String fieldName; // Note that Field names are to be qualified // with the Namespace name, as an example: // http://www.ipdr.org/namespace:movieId // The namespace MUST match one of those // targeted by the schema or schema imports boolean isEnabled // true=enabled Field false=disabled Field }
ProtocolMsgHeaderOnly The class is a common ancestor for all IPDR protocol messages which contain only the header Consult ProtocolMsg for exact header structure.
ProtocolMsgKEEPALIVE The class represents a KEEPALIVE message
ProtocolMsgMODIFY_TEMPLATE The class represents the MODIFY_TEMPLATE message
ProtocolMsgMODIFY_TEMPLATE_RESPONSE The class represents the MODIFY_TEMPLATE_RESPONSE message
ProtocolMsgSESSION_START  
ProtocolMsgSESSION_STOP  
ProtocolMsgSTART_NEGOTIATION The class represents a START_NEGOTIATION message
ProtocolMsgSTART_NEGOTIATION_REJECT The class represents a START_NEGOTIATION_REJECT message
ProtocolMsgTemplate The class is a common ancestor of all classes which contain a template block.
ProtocolMsgTEMPLATE_DATA The class represents the TEMPLATE_DATA message
ProtocolMsgVERSION_REQUEST The class represents IPDR VERSION_REQUEST message.
ProtocolMsgVERSION_RESPONSE The class represents IPDR VERSION_RESPONSE message The message has the following structure: struct VersionResponse { ProtocolInfo defaultProtocol; ProtocolInfo [] additionalProtocols; } struct ProtocolInfo { int transportType; int protocolVersion; short portNumber; short reserved; }
ProtocolSessionInfo Represents a session info block for GetSessions message
ProtocolStreamMsg The Java encapsulation of a IPDR protocol message over TCP The message has the common header: struct IPDRStreamingHeader { char version; // version of protocol, for this version, set to 2 char messageId; // the ID of this Message (see MessageIds) char sessionId; // the ID of this Session or 0 if not Session-specific char messageFlags; // reserved/unused and set to 0 int messageLen; // length in bytes of Message including header }
 

Exception Summary
ConnectionException Represents a connection-level exception
DataException Exception thrown when there's an error in the protocol data.
InvalidCapabilities Represents session-level exception for situations when exporter and/or collector capabilites are invalid
InvalidSessionStateException Indicates invalid state transition or message for a session.
PeerSessionErrorException Represents session-level exception upon error message sent by peer
ProtocolMalformedMsgException The exception for giving information about a mal-formed message.
SessionException
